			<h2>Correspondence</h2>
			<a class="xsmall link-alt" href="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor">Write a Letter to the Editor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>
		</div>

		<div id="article-correspondences" class="correspondences correspondences-collapsed">
								<div class="block-correspondence" id="2466">
		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p>I find <strong>The Sun</strong>&rsquo;s new design elegant and full of style and character. The writing in the February 1999 issue was beautiful, too, especially Mirabai Starr&rsquo;s &ldquo;<a href="/article/2074">The Disappearing God</a>.&rdquo; Her story is all too common: that of a serious seeker who tries to find God in other people only to discover that all gurus disappoint in the end. I wish every spiritual seeker could learn to locate God, as Starr did, in the expression of lovingkindness during difficult moments.</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">John Stilwell<br>New York, New York</p>
					</blockquote>
	</div>

					</div>

